Text.Value: You are.
*You realise you're talking to an intellect devourer, a minion of the mind flayers who abducted you.*
Don't leave us, please don't. Please don't leave us.
We must go to the helm. At the helm we are needed.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Open to interpretatoin) The player digs a finger into the side of the brain, pressing on something inside it).

Text.Value: Hngah...

EditorData.NodeContext: Death gasp of a man whose brain has just become an intellect devourer and run away.

Text.Value: All right, let's go.
Who am I talking to - a man or a brain?
What should I call you?
I helped you once, but that's all I can do.
Do you not hear it? We will not survive here. We are needed to navigate - we are needed to leave this realm.
Attempt a cerebral extraction, staying mindful of the swelling.
*The brain won't budge.*
*You know no creature like this - one that is more brain than person.*
*The creature pauses, listening. Something behind your eye seizes in recognition.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shot focused on the brain, which should be tensed. Player might wince.
~The player hits the side of the skull trying break a piece of bone loose to free the brain.

Text.Value: You are us. Friend.
No! We are us! We must survive!
We must go to the helm. We must navigate the ship. We must leave this place.
*Your fingers twitch with the desire to rip its tender, moist meat to shreds.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Added the 'TalkedToIntellectDevourer' check here to exclude Duergar and Gith that have already recognised that it's an intellect devourer [SR]

Text.Value: Leave.
Us. Together. We must leave this place. We must be safe.
No. You have to stay here.
I think you're past the point of saving. Tell me what to do.
What do you want from me, exactly?
Destroy the brain.
Us. We are us.
*The exposed brain quivers in expectation.*
*You notice oedema - a swelling of the brain causing pressure where it strains against the shell of the skull.*
I'll go - but not with you.
*Apart from this strange context, you notice nothing unusual about the brain.*
You sound afraid. Why?
*The brain lifts from the skull, but you notice an opportunity - you could cripple the strange creature, making it more subservient should it prove a threat.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~The player gingerly pries the brain from the skull
EditorData.SFXTags: Brain mushing sounds, blood, skull creaking

Text.Value: A pet of ghaik scum. Destroy the intellect devourer while it's vulnerable.
Kill the mind flayer slave before the corruption spreads.
Remove us from this body - from this case free us. Please!
*SCREECH!*
*The brain tenses, as though querying an unseen advisor.*
Yes! You've come to save us from this place, from this place you'll free us!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A man is strapped to a chair, his skull cracked open, brain exposed to the elements. A voice fills the players' head - it is disjointed, genderless, neither whispered nor shouted.

Text.Value: You are no friend of mine, creature.
I'm not like you.
To the helm we go. We are going to the helm.
Attack the brain anyway.
Do nothing for me. Do everything for us.
*The creature seems unaware of your interference. It relaxes in your hands.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player continues lifting hte brain from the skull and sets the intellect devourer on the ground.

Text.Value: What's at the helm?
*The swelling is too great. You cannot lift the brain out of the skull.*
Spare the creature - any injuries might weaken it.
*With a start, you realise you're talking to an intellect devourer, a minion of the mind flayers who abducted you.*
*You realise you are talking to a brain rather than a person - but you know no creature like this.*
Attack the brain.
*The skull holds fast.*
We are free. Our freedom is ours. Friend.
*Screech!*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~The player jams their fingers into the grey matter and minces the strange creature in it's cranial crib

Text.Value: Fine. Let's go.
Break the skull.
Imagine a brain full of holes. A brain like your own.
Inspect the exposed brain.
Gently prise the brain from the skull.
A newborn. Born new from this husk.
Please, before they return. They return.
The enemy. So many enemies.
Mutilate the brain.
We listen to our friend. Our friend who saved us.
Why must you survive?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~The player reaches their hands into the victim's head and tries to wrench the brain free, but it won't budge

Synopsis: Players find a humanoid strapped to an operation chamber, his skull opened to reveal his brain. When starting a dialogue with the humanoid, they will hear a strange voice in their mind. Through investigation they can learn this to be an intellect devourer trapped in the man's skull. The player can assist in liberating the intellect devourer and gain it as a follower for the duration of the tutorial or kill it.
